cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.GR, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with triangulating a set of points in the plane and maintaining the triangulation as the points move continuously. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and the use of a kinetic data structure suggests a connection to control and dynamical systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions Davenport-Schinzel sequences, which are related to combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of a randomized scheme and analysis of expected number of changes suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of a triangulation suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.GR).
